  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut approx. 400g<span class=\"text-danger\"> [800g]<strong> </span>cauliflower</strong> into large florets and line a baking tray with <strong>tin foil</strong> or <strong>baking paper</strong></p><p>Combine 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[180ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> in a bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix everything together – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a plate with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>salt </strong>and 3 <span class=\"text-danger\">[6] </span>generous grinds of <strong>black pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> salt & pepper coating</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong> to the<strong> </strong>batter,<strong> </strong>coating them all over, then dip them in the salt & pepper coating and transfer to the lined baking tray – this is your <strong>salt & pepper cauliflower</strong></p><p>Drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
